<item>
            <title>[LU-7972] $REFORMAT in t-f is not used correctly</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7972</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;$REFORMAT is defined in test-framework.sh and used in the following code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ! is_mounted $MOUNT &amp;amp;&amp;amp; ! is_mounted $MOUNT2; then
        [ &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;$REFORMAT&quot;&lt;/span&gt; ] &amp;amp;&amp;amp; formatall
        # setupall mounts both MOUNT and MOUNT2 (&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; MOUNT_2 is set)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is an issue that even if we set &quot;REFORMAT=no&quot;, it will still format all.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will submit a patch to fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
